                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Balt.</placeName>\n                                        <date>Aug 24<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1848</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p> Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Your esteemed fav. Of <date>20th</date><lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add> have sooner elicited a letter to <persName>Mr\n                                                  Hart</persName><lb/> (one accompanies this) has\n                                        the proximity<add>?</add><lb/> both from the uncertainty in\n                                        which you stood as<lb/> to the more commanding claims of\n                                        your own Congr,<lb/> and our own as the day had not been\n                                                  <add>?</add><lb/> fixed until <persName>Mr\n                                                  Jonas</persName> return. I have not been<lb/> able\n                                        to name any definite day until now.</p>\n                              <p>We had been desirous to select the second <add>?</add><lb/> for\n                                        several reasons of greater convenience but<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mr J</persName> wishes to be in <placeName>N.\n                                                  O.</placeName> by the <date>2nd<add>?</add>\n                                                  Oct.</date> when<lb/> his business requires his\n                                        presence, &amp; he has<lb/> promised to give a week to his\n                                        friend in <placeName>Cini.</placeName><lb/> so we have been\n                                                  over<add>?</add>. the <sic>rether</sic> as he\n                                        informs<lb/> us you prefer the first wednesday as more<lb/>\n                                        convenient to your self and <persName>Conn.</persName> you\n                                        will<lb/> we hope take the occasion to spend a few days<lb/>\n                                        with us, we will provide you quarters either<lb/> with\n                                                  <persName>E. P. Cohen</persName> or <persName>Mr\n                                                  Bordley's</persName>, as the former<lb/> has\n                                        removed to a larger house,, I have no doubt<lb/> he\n                                                  <add>?</add> will be happy to house you with\n                                        them<lb/> let us know however if you object to either</p>\n                              <p>A marriage before night will be productive of<lb/> a great deal of\n                                        inconvenience to us as we are<lb/> situated &amp; we have\n                                        consulted <persName>Mr Rice</persName> who</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3x63bn64/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
